Nuclear Cyborg
Corp
Privacy Policy
Effective: February 11,
2025
Collection
and Use of Personal Information
Personal information is data that can be used to identify or
contact a single person.
You may be asked to provide your personal information anytime
you are in contact with Nuclear Cyborg Corp or a Nuclear Cyborg Corp affiliated
company.
Nuclear Cyborg Corp and its
affiliates may share this personal information with each other and use it consistent
with this Privacy Policy.
They may also
combine it with other information to provide and improve our products,
services, content, and advertising.
You
are not required to provide the personal information that we have requested,
but, if you chose not to do so, in many cases we will not be able to provide
you with our products or services or respond to any queries you may have.
Here are some examples of the types of personal information Nuclear
Cyborg Corp may collect and how we may use it:
What personal
information we collect
·
When
you create a Nuclear Cyborg Corp account, purchase a product, download a
software update, contact us, or participate in an online survey, chat room, or
forum, we may collect a variety of information, including your name, mailing
address, phone number, email address, contact preferences, age and/or date of
birth, gender, social media account identifiers, and credit card / payment information.
·
When
you upload or post photos, videos, or audio recordings to our apps, websites,
forums, social media, or chat groups.
·
When
you share your content with family and friends using Nuclear Cyborg Corp
products, send gift certificates and products, or invite others to participate
in Nuclear Cyborg Corp services or forums, Nuclear Cyborg Corp may collect the
information you provide about those people such as name, mailing address, email
address, and phone number.
Nuclear
Cyborg Corp will use such information to fulfill your requests, provide the
relevant product or service, or for anti-fraud purposes.
·
When
you purchase or lease our apps, in-app purchases, subscriptions, services,
upgrades, or products, we collect information about the transaction, such as
identifiers, date/time, prices, and currency.
For products purchased outside of the Apple App Store or Google Play, we
may collect your name, phone number, email and/or account identifier, payment
details, billing address, and shipping, delivery, and fulfillment details.
·
In certain
jurisdictions, we may ask for a government issued ID in limited circumstances
as required by law.
·
For financial
services and apps, such as Mortgage Calculator for Pros, we never collect,
use
or share your personal financial information.
·
For
developer services and apps, such as Pricing for App Store Connect, we do not
collect, share, or use any of your financial data, such as app pricing, sales units,
sales dollar volumes, or your app revenue.
We do collect some metadata, such as the number of apps, in-app
purchases, and subscriptions, to help us understand how our apps and services
are used.
How we
use your personal information
·
The
personal information we collect allows us to keep you posted on Nuclear Cyborg
Corp’s latest product announcements, software updates, and upcoming events.
If you don’t want to be on our mailing list,
you can opt out anytime by contacting us.
·
We also
use personal information to help us create, develop, operate, deliver, and
improve our apps, products, services, content, advertising, and for loss
prevention and anti-fraud purposes.
·
We may
use your personal information, including date of birth, to verify identity,
assist with identification of users, and to determine appropriate services.
For example, we may use date of birth to
determine the age of Nuclear Cyborg Corp ID account holders.
·
From
time to time, we may use your personal information to send important notices,
such as communications about purchases and changes to our terms, conditions,
and policies.
Because this information
is important to your interaction with Nuclear Cyborg Corp, you may not opt out
of receiving these communications.
·
We may
also use personal information for internal purposes such as auditing, data
analysis, and research to improve Nuclear Cyborg Corp’s products, services, and
customer communications.
·
If you
enter a sweepstake, contest, or similar promotion we may use the information
you provide to administer those programs.
We
retain personal information for as long as needed to deliver or operate the
app, software, or service.
For example,
if you have a Nuclear Cyborg Corp account, all personal information associated with
your account will be retained for as long as you have the account, plus
additional time to allow for handling of customer service issues.
If your
account has been sanctioned for violations of our Terms of Use or User
Agreement, information about the sanction will be retained indefinitely, even
if you delete your account.
We may
retain personal information to resolve disputes, enforce our Terms of Use,
Privacy Policy, or any applicable app-specific or service-specific User
Agreement, or to comply with a legal requirement.
Collection and Use of
Non-Personal Information
We also collect data in a form that does not, on its own, permit
direct association with any specific individual.
We may collect, use, transfer, and disclose
non-personal information for any purpose. The following are some examples of
non-personal information that we collect and how we may use it:
·
We may
collect information such as device type, model, hardware configuration, date
and time, operating system, version, operating system configuration, network
address, vendor-specific device identifier, occupation, language, zip code,
area code, platform-specific advertising identifier (if permitted by you),
referrer URL, location, and the time zone where a Nuclear Cyborg Corp product
is used so that we can better understand customer behavior and improve our
products, services, and advertising.
·
We may
collect information regarding customer activities on our website, interactions
with the iTunes Store, App Store, MAC App Store, Google Play app store, Amazon
app store, and others for Nuclear Cyborg Corp.
This information is aggregated and used to
help us provide more useful information to our customers and to understand
which parts of our apps, website, products, and services are of most interest.
Aggregated data is considered non‑personal information for the purposes of this
Privacy Policy.
·
We may
collect data about how you use our Apps, applications, software, and websites
to help us improve them and to present you with relevant advertising
content.
Such data may include, but is
not limited to, App launch time, number of times App is launched, individual
and aggregate session lengths, details of which features of the app you engaged
with, including whether or not you shared the App or parts of your activity
within the App via social media or other channels, details of your In-App
Purchases, including which items were purchased and the amount of money spent,
as well as details regarding advertisements requested, displayed, and
interacted with.
For games, this data
may also include high scores, which levels or game parts were passed or failed
including the number of times, details on the receiving and spending of in-game
virtual currencies, and any other interaction within the game or App.
If we do combine non-personal information with personal
information the combined information will be treated as personal information
for as long as it remains combined.
We may retain non-personal data indefinitely.
Cookies
and Other Technologies
Nuclear Cyborg Corp’s websites, online services, interactive
applications, email messages, and advertisements may use cookies and other
similar technologies, such as pixel tags and web beacons. These technologies
help us better understand user behavior, tell us which parts of our websites
people have visited, and facilitate and measure the effectiveness of
advertisements and web searches.
We
treat information collected by cookies and other technologies as non‑personal
information.
However, to the extent that
Internet Protocol (IP) addresses or similar identifiers are considered personal
information by local law, we also treat these identifiers as personal
information. Similarly, to the extent that non-personal information is combined
with personal information, we treat the combined information as personal
information for the purposes of this Privacy Policy.
On iOS devices, we may request that you consent to using the
devices Advertising Identifier.
You can choose to deny this consent by enabling Limit Ad
Tracking (prior to iOS 14.5) or Ask App Not to Track (App Tracking
Transparency, iOS 14.5 and later), or responding appropriately if you are
prompted by the app.
If you enable this feature on your mobile device, third-party
apps, such as those provided by Nuclear Cyborg Corp, cannot use the device’s Advertising
Identifier to serve you targeted ads.
You
will still see the same number of ads, but the ads may be less relevant to you.
If you consent to this tracking and later wish to withdraw
consent, you may do so in the device’s Settings at any time.
Nuclear Cyborg Corp and our partners also use cookies and other
technologies to remember personal information when you use our website, online
services, and applications.
Our goal in
these cases is to make your experience with Nuclear Cyborg Corp more convenient
and personal.
For example, knowing your
first name lets us welcome you the next time you visit the Nuclear Cyborg Corp sites
and stores.
Knowing your country and
language − and if you are an educator, your school − helps us provide a
customized and more useful shopping experience.
Knowing someone using your computer or device
has shopped for a certain product or used a particular service helps us make
our advertising and email communications more relevant to your interests.
And knowing your contact information, and
information about your computer or device helps us personalize your app
experience, and provide you with better customer service.
Check with your browser provider to find out how to disable
cookies. Please note that certain features of Nuclear Cyborg Corp websites will
not be available once cookies are disabled.
As is true of most internet services, we gather some information
automatically and store it in log files. This information includes Internet
Protocol (IP) addresses, browser type and language, Internet service provider
(ISP), referring and exit websites and applications, operating system,
date/time stamp, and clickstream data.
We use this information to understand and analyze trends, to
administer the site, to learn about user behavior on the site, to improve our
product and services, and to gather demographic information about our user base
as a whole.
Nuclear Cyborg Corp may use
this information in our marketing and advertising services.
In some of our email messages, we use a “click-through URL”
linked to content on the Nuclear Cyborg Corp website.
When customers click one of these URLs, they
pass through a separate web server before arriving at the destination page on
our website.
This separate server may be
owned and operated by Nuclear Cyborg Corp or may be owned and operated by a third-party
data processor.
We track this
click-through data to help us determine interest in particular topics and
measure the effectiveness of our customer communications. If you prefer not to
be tracked in this way, you should not click text or graphic links in the email
messages.
Pixel tags enable us to send email messages in a format
customers can read, and they tell us whether mail has been opened.
We may use this information to reduce or
eliminate messages sent to customers.
Biometrics
and Face Data
No Nuclear Cyborg Corp apps collect, store,
transmit, or share any biometric or face data.
The app “Santa Face Live Moji Mask” uses live
face data to animate a 3D cartoon face and head model with the same movements
and expressions as the user’s face.
This
data is processed ephemerally, on-device, while the app is running, and is then
immediately discarded.
Additionally,
neither the animated cartoon expressions nor the videos created by the user are
transmitted off-device, except as directed by the user’s sharing actions within
the app.
Disclosure
to Third Parties
Nuclear Cyborg Corp may make certain information available to third
party service providers and data processor partners that work with Nuclear
Cyborg Corp to provide products and services, or that help Nuclear Cyborg Corp
market to customers.
Except as already
described, personal information will only be shared by Nuclear Cyborg Corp to
provide or improve our software, products, and services.
Service
Providers / Data Processors
Nuclear Cyborg Corp shares personal information with companies
who provide services such as analytics, advertising, information processing,
extending credit, fulfilling customer orders, delivering products to you,
managing customer data, providing customer service, assessing your interest in
our products and services, and conducting customer research or satisfaction
surveys.
These companies are obligated
to protect your information and may be located wherever Nuclear Cyborg Corp
operates.
