Others
It may be necessary − by law, legal process, litigation, and/or
requests from public and governmental authorities within or outside your
country of residence, and/or requests from platform operators (such as Apple,
Google, etc.) − for Nuclear Cyborg Corp to disclose your personal information.
We may also disclose information about you if
we determine that for purposes of national security, law enforcement, or other
issues of public importance, or for compliance with Apple App Store or Google
Play store compliance, disclosure is necessary or appropriate.
We may also disclose information about you if we determine that
disclosure is reasonably necessary to enforce our terms and conditions or
protect our operations or users.
Additionally, in the event of a reorganization,
merger, or sale we may transfer all personal information we collect to the new
entity.
Third
Party Websites and Services
N
uclear Cyborg Corp software, such as apps and websites, may
contain
a
dvertisements which link to websites and other
apps that are operated by third parties.
We do not control and accept no liability or responsibility for those
websites and apps, and this Privacy Policy does not apply to those websites and
apps.
Please consult the terms and
conditions and privacy policy of such third-party websites and apps to find out
how they collect and use your personal data and to establish what they may use
your personal data for.
Protection
of Personal Information
Nuclear Cyborg Corp takes the security of your personal
information very seriously.
Nuclear
Cyborg Corp online services protect your personal information during transit
using encryption such as Transport Layer Security (TLS).
When you use some Nuclear Cyborg Corp products, services, or
applications or post on a Nuclear Cyborg Corp forum, chat room, or social
networking service, the personal information and content you share is visible
to other users and can be read, collected, or used by them. You are responsible
for the personal information you choose to share or submit in these instances.
For example, if you list your name and email address in a forum posting, that
information is public.
Please take care
when using these features.
If you log on to a device that is owned by a third party, any
information you access, display, upload, or download while using that third
party device may be accessible by other users, thereby disclosing that
information.
Your login credentials, such as password, Pass Key, or other
authentication method, whether used directly to access a Nuclear Cyborg Corp
app or service, or whether to unlock your device generally, is your
responsibility.
Children
& Education
We understand the importance of taking extra precautions to
protect the privacy and safety of children using Nuclear Cyborg Corp products
and services.
Children under the age of
13, or equivalent minimum age in the relevant jurisdiction, are not permitted
to create their own Nuclear Cyborg Corp accounts, unless their parent provided
verifiable consent.
If we learn that we
have collected the personal information of a child under 13, or equivalent
minimum age depending on jurisdiction, outside the above circumstances, we will
take steps to delete the information as soon as possible.
If at any time a parent needs to access, correct, or delete data
associated with their child’s account may contact us.
Location-Based
Services
To provide location-based services on Nuclear Cyborg Corp
products, Nuclear Cyborg Corp and our partners and licensees may collect, use,
and share precise location data, including the real-time geographic location of
your computer or device.
Where
available, location-based services may use GPS, Bluetooth, and your IP Address,
along with crowd-sourced Wi-Fi hotspot and cell tower locations, and other
technologies to determine your devices’ approximate location.
Unless you have completed a Facebook login
through the App, provided an email address, or otherwise explicitly provided
consent, this location data is collected anonymously in a form that does not
personally identify you and is used by Nuclear Cyborg Corp and our partners and
licensees to provide and improve location-based products and services, and to
provide the most relevant advertising offers to you.
Third‑Party
Sites and Services
Nuclear Cyborg Corp websites, products, applications, and
services may contain links to third-party websites, products, and services.
Our products and services may also use or
offer products or services from third parties − for example, a third‑party app.
Information collected by third parties, which may include such
things as location data or contact details, is governed by their privacy practices,
not ours.
We encourage you to learn
about the privacy practices of those third parties.
If you purchase a subscription within one of our Apps, we create
a Subscriber ID that is unique to you and which includes information about the
subscription you purchased, and your country of residence. This information is
provided so we, as the developer, can understand the performance of our
subscriptions.
International
Users
All the information you provide may be transferred or accessed
by entities around the world as described in this Privacy Policy.
Personal
Data Deletion & Privacy Questions
Most of our apps don’t collect personal
information.
For those that do or require an account to
function, launch the app and go to Settings and choose Delete my Account.
If you don’t see that option or the app
doesn’t have a Settings screen, then that app doesn’t collect personal
information.
In most cases, deleting the
app from your device also deletes most data associated with that app.
To request deletion of personal data associated with you, or if
you have any questions or concerns about Nuclear Cyborg Corp’s Privacy Policy
or data processing or if you would like to make a complaint about a possible
breach of local privacy laws, contact us at:
info@nuclearcyborg.com
Nuclear Cyborg Corp
3760 Rosewood Ln N, Plymouth, MN 55441, USA
All such communications are reviewed, and replies issued where
appropriate, as soon as possible, but generally within 30 days.
If you are requesting deletion of personal
data, we will require proof of your identity, which may include a valid
government-issued photo ID and/or other documentation.
Changes
to our Privacy Policy
Nuclear Cyborg Corp may update its Privacy Policy from time to
time.
By accessing our websites,
applications (apps) and services, you consent to our collection and use of your
information as described in this Privacy Policy.
